article.headline: Western Illinois 85, Centenary 68
article.story: SHREVEPORT, La. (AP) -- Eulis Baez scored 24 points and grabbed 12 rebounds to lead Western Illinois to an 85-68 victory over Centenary on Thursday night, snapping the Leathernecks' 28-game road losing streak. Western Illinois (7-11, 3-4 Mid-Con) led 41-32 at halftime and took control of the game in the first four minutes of the second half, building its lead to 53-39 after a lay-up and three-pointer by Troy Okeson. Fred Oguns added 15 points and T.J. gray 13 for Western Illinois, which shot 56.9 percent from the field and outrebounded Centenary 35-37. Tyrone Hamilton scored 29 points for Centenary (2-17, 0-8), including 18 in the second half. He hit four 3-pointers. Chad Maclies added 17 points and 11 rebounds. <
